# Grasp Primitive Service
# Wraps the official allegro_hand_control_msgs/action/GraspCommand action so it
# can be triggered via a single blocking ROS 2 service call from RobotEnv-style
# clients (matching the franka_gripper grasp/open/close ergonomics).

# Posture/grasp primitive name. Routed by allegro_hand_interface_node:
#   - posture controller (position-based): home, ready, off
#   - grasp controller   (effort-based)  : grasp_3, grasp_4, pinch_it, pinch_mt, envelop
string command

# Desired envelop grasp torque (only meaningful for effort-mode primitives).
# -1 (default) → use the controller's built-in default.
float64 effort

# Whether to block until the action completes
bool blocking
---
bool success
string message
bool stalled       # Mirrors the action result
bool reached_goal  # Mirrors the action result
